{
  "stem": "24515.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I mean, that nonsense about Aryan girls and Jewish, with that, what I told you before, that my mother said don't you, you know, look at or talk to or let alone, touch, any girl.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I suppose that affects me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- I forget it was the Nuremberg laws, I mean, yes, I have a feeling it was a Nuremberg law that Jews were told they were no longer [GERMAN], that is free, recognized citizens.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they are sort of-- something, it's a slightly different word.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I've forgotten right now what it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Volks-- ?] no, it was the other way around.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were not [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Volks ?] [GERMAN], that is, belonging to the people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were simply and only citizens of the state, that kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Again, I can't think of anything specific that this-- that changed in my life.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You see, what it obviously did was, it made it less and less easy or possible to deal-- to deal with, to talk to non-Jewish youngsters.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I remember one very bright youngster asked me to come to his house to talk to him about the Jews, because what he had heard.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he wanted to check out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He wanted to check on it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That boy was unusual.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was very brave.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Or his parents were, or both were.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I did go to his house.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had an hour's conversation or something like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he thanked me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, you know, that was it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there's that, I suppose.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, the social life was [? affected. ?] Then of course, we never knew how long we could stay in the German school.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
